'''''Berserker Raids''''' is a [[turn-based strategy]] video game designed by LLoyd Johnson and [[Fred Saberhagen]] for the [[Apple II series|Apple II]] and  published by Baen Software in 1983.<ref name="manual">{{cite book |title=Berserker Raids Player's Manual |date=1983 |publisher=Baen Software |url=https://archive.org/details/berserker_raids_manual/mode/2up}}</ref> It was ported to the [[Atari 8-bit computers]], [[Commodore 64]], and [[MS-DOS]].

==Gameplay==
''Berserker Raids'' is a game in which automated machines operate as murderous space fortresses, based on short stories written by [[Fred Saberhagen]] in the 1960s.<ref name="CGW22"/>

==Reception==
Jasper Sylvester reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "I wouldn't hesitate to recommend Berserker Raids to any Saberhagen or space conquest fan."<ref name="CGW22">{{cite magazine |last=Sylvester |first=Jasper |title=Micro-Reviews |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=June–July 1985 |volume=1 |issue=22 |pages=34–35}}</ref>

